---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About - SkanPay"
  description="SkanPay focuses on QR code payment gateway experiences for merchants, mobile wallets, and payment partners."
  activePath="/about/"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About SkanPay</p>
    <h1>Focused on practical QR payment experiences</h1>
    <p>SkanPay works around a simple idea: mobile payment experiences should be easier to connect with physical checkout moments.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <h2>Built around the payment moment</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">The company focuses on QR payment gateway conversations for merchants, payment apps, mobile wallets, and loyalty-driven commerce.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="split-panel">
      <h3>What guides the work</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Make the checkout flow understandable for merchants and customers.</li>
        <li>Keep payment claims clear, accurate, and grounded.</li>
        <li>Support partner conversations with practical operational language.</li>
        <li>Give interested organizations a direct path to start a conversation.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Company posture</p>
        <h2>Credibility through clarity</h2>
      </div>
      <p>SkanPay should be easy to understand before a merchant, partner, or stakeholder asks for technical detail.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid three">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Merchant-first language</h3>
        <p>The site starts with the people operating the checkout experience.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Partner-ready framing</h3>
        <p>Payment apps and loyalty platforms can see where their customer relationships might fit.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Measured claims</h3>
        <p>The website avoids unsupported processing, compliance, or customer claims until they are confirmed.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
